   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 14. The Least Squares Criterion\n",
    "\n",
    "The Method of Least Squares selects b0 and b1 that minimize SSE.\n",
    "\n",
    "Thus: The best-fitting regression line is the line with the smallest total squared prediction error.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is one of the foundational optimization principles in all of statistics and machine learning."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Find and display the least squares line\n",
    "least_squares_model = LinearRegression()\n",
    "least_squares_model.fit(df_demo[['X']], df_demo['Y'])\n",
    "\n",
    "ls_b0 = least_squares_model.intercept_\n",
    "ls_b1 = least_squares_model.coef_[0]\n",
    "ls_pred = least_squares_model.predict(df_demo[['X']])\n",
    "ls_sse = np.sum((df_demo['Y'] - ls_pred)**2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"LEAST SQUARES REGRESSION LINE\")\n",
